__DESCRIPTION__

Timm Murray's talk on using encryption in Perl for the Madison Perl Mongers
2014 April 09.

The talk is based on the <b>Perl Encryption Primer</b> articles:

* [The Importance of Randomness](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/12/perl-encryption-primer-the-importance-of-randomness/)
* [One Time Pads Are Too Awesome To Use](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/19/perl-encryption-primer-one-time-pads-are-too-awesome-to-use/)
* [Block Ciphers](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/21/perl-encryption-primer-block-ciphers/)
* [Public Key Encryption](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/25/perl-encryption-primer-public-key-encryption/)
* [Hashes](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/27/perl-encryption-primer-hashes/)
* [Passwords](http://www.wumpus-cave.net/2014/03/31/perl-encryption-primer-passwords/)

